text.tspan: Exponents are used to denote the repeated multiplication of a number by itself;

text.tspan: In the expression 2⁴ , 2 is called the base, 4 is called the exponent, and we read the expression as “2 to the fourth power.”

text.style: -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); text-anchor: middle; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; cursor: pointer;
text.tspan: So 3 to the third power is 27.

text.tspan: When negative numbers are raised to powers, the result may be positive or negative
